reviews:
Just a few minutes walks from Bonne Nouvelle metro station. Easy and convenient to travel. Warm and friendly staff, delicious breakfast. Very unique boutique hotel!
I can't remember a front desk agent who helped me with check-out. She was very kind. Also other staff members were friendly. Thank you Hotel Echiquier Opera Paris MGallery!

Fabulous little hotel in a really good location. We walked everywhere with the louvre and seine about a 30 minute walk away and an easy hour door to door commute from Orly. Lovely decor in a modern 20s style including original lift. Everything was very clean and the service quietly attentive. The most generous beautiful breakfast with an amazing selection of sweet and savory options. Our room was small but blissfully quiet andhad everything we needed and the shower was lovely. Loads of local restaurants and bars nearby. They lay on coffee and cake in the afternoon which is a nice touch. Would recommend bistro kinzo for an unusual Japanese fusion tasting treat - very close by. Would recommend.

Excellent customer service . The front desk offered us great advise on things to do and scheduling transportation . The food from the afternoon tea to the breakfast buffet was very tasty and of high quality . The hotel
Is quite and close to many small interesting places to eat and shop .

The hotel was the perfect size for 3 women for a long weekend - we were quite happy with that. Amenities were good and the staff were nice. The only problems we encountered which were the only reasons for the lower ratings were that the hot water was turned off for a short period right around the time we checked in and we weren’t informed it was happening, so my friend had hopped in the shower after her long flight to the shock of cold water - I called the front desk and they said it had been temporarily shut off but would return soon (and it did, about 10-15 minutes later). But, I found it odd not to be informed. The thermostat also did not work in our room (405), there was no control of hot or cold. In mid April, we made due with the windows being open to release some heat and humidity, but this would be totally unreasonable in summer months. I’ve seen this complaint in other reviews as well, so I didn’t even call the front desk about it (because again, with the window open it was fine), but I find this pretty unacceptable for a 4 star hotel.

Stayed for a week for our wedding anniversary. Loved the staff and hotel. Very pleasant and helpful. The location is a bit off the beaten track but we liked that as it felt less hectic than central Paris. Breakfast room and service is also great. Would definitely return.

Hotel staff, service, cleanness are all top notch. It’s an old building, there is not much you can do, but Hotel service are more than enough to compensate that.

One thing America hotels need learn is unlike them, European hotels are bringing service back to precovid level, while many US hotels are still living in covid days, from room service, breakfast, etc to save money.

You get much better service here.

MGallery L Echiquier was a nice surprise : an hotel with a parisian atmosphere where you feel immediately welcome thanks to a competent staff. Bar/Breakfast room is full of charm, with quality products. Rooms are comfortable, with big bathrooms (not the traditional tiny shower room you have in plenty of hotels in paris). All in all, very good experience to reiter (two streets from there, plenty of restaurants ...).

This hotel is great! Beautiful decor and close to a good metro station.

Paul at reception is amazing!! So friendly and helpful and always so attentive. Made a request to clean the room while we went out and when we got back everything was perfect even in the night! He definitely made our stay.

We are currently staying at hotel for one more night. Starting with positive, the front desk staff are amazing and super helpful they have assisted in helping us navigate restaurants metro and walks. The beds and pillows are super comfy! Only tiny negative is the bar staff and service is exceptionally slow, even if you are practically they only guest in bar it may take 10 minutes before anyone comes over to take order, this is while they are standing behind bar, strange?
Also had sent in request prior to arriving regarding the purpose of trip and it’s special nature and although not a deal breaker this wasn’t acknowledged. Most hotels when I have sent prior information they acknowledge even with a short note left in room.
Again not to be overly critical

This hotel is fantastic. A little out of the way but a few minutes walk from the Bonne Nouvelle Tube station and loads of nearby dining options.
The staff is fantastic and helpful, with warm greetings all day.
Ate in the restaurant and the food was good and served quickly. The daily breakfast was phenomenal and massive.
The rooms are smal but well appointed and comfortable. And enjoyed every minute of my stay.

My husband and I stayed in this hotel over the Christmas holiday. The staff couldn't have been nicer and more helpful. The breakfast was delicious! It was seriously the best hotel breakfast we'd ever had. The rooms were a decent size for Paris and the hotel itself was beautiful decorated. The location is in a more locals area so it will be necessary to take the Metro into the more touristed areas of the city. Fortunately there is a Metro stop within walking distance of the hotel. What's nice about the location is that you can easily walk to restaurants and bars that are reasonable priced and delicious!

Great location and excellent customer service. Family friendly and welcoming. Comfortable beds. Nice luxury bathroom products. High water pressure. After noon tea was nice ( some of the service at the bar could be better. ) great stay and we will definitely come back.

Hotel has excellent facilities. Rooms are comfortable. Breakfast has items available for all types of guests. Staff has helping attitude. Location of hotel is also convenient being close to food and shopping outlets.

The staff at this hotel were excellent. Very nice people and very helpful. The rooms were nice and the area not as noisy as central Paris. They offer a breakfast each day as well. They also have tea in the afternoons. Lots of places to eat or shop nearby.

Really lovely hotel. Modern take on belle epoque style. Comfiest bed & pillow I’ve had in a hotel yet. Staff friendly & helpful with advice on trips & travel. Incredibly got room with 3 single beds- all great quality- in our twin deluxe room for 3. Clarins toiletries. Great location- v convenient for Bonne Nouvelle Metro (or St Denis if needing to buy tickets). Eurodisney easily reached in an hour via Metro the RER A & although got taxi from airport, return via Metro to Gare du Nord & RER B to CDG airport was also v easy

Used to travel in Accor hotel, this place has now become my new favorite place in Paris !
The hotel staff is very thoughful (from the reception to the restaurant) and cheerful ! Always a pressure to interact with them.

The reception team was amazing ! They were really helpful and profesional. From my arrival to my departure they were always there and we can feel that they are doing their job with passion ! They knew what they were doing.

Thank you again for my amazing stay ! I Will definitely come back !

We have stayed 5 nights at L’Echiquier and was absolutely top notch from the day we made the reservation until the checkout.
Reception staff is exceptional, customer service could not be more efficient.
Location is great, very central and metro station is also nearby.
I recommend this place for any kind of voyage, business or leisure.
We will definitely be back.

We stayed in room 215 (Superior room) for a few nights, room was very good, well equipped, great bathroom, great shower and efficient a/c. Bed was very comfortable. No street noise. Elevators, (there are two) of which one is exceptionally quaint and travels up through staircase. Bar is very eclectic with great choice of drinks including cocktails. Reception staff were excellent and made our stay even better.

Highly recommended hotel with good location next to historical part of Paris and its fashion stores. Skilled and customer orientated personnel as well as good breakfast helped to stay positive during our journey.

We spent a few nights in a Suite at the Hotel L'Echiquier Opera Paris. That was a bit of a disappointment overall.

I waited 15 minutes to be checked-in, due to angry customers checking out with interestingly similar issues about overcharges.

During the check-in process, I was not recognized as a top tier member (I am a Diamond Accor member). There was no welcome amenity (I did not bother asking). The minibar was empty the first day and magically went full on the second.

I requested a late checkout over the phone on the day before we left, I was told "3PM". The next morning, asking for my room key to be reprogrammed, I am told "1PM". The lady I spoke to wasn't apologetic or did not try to help, I was only faced with: "Look at what's written on my computer".

Then came checkout time, and I was having "deja vu". Some erroneous items added to my bill like breakfasts (I did not have breakfast on-site, on any day).

All-in-all, the Hotel L'Echiquier Opera Paris is a solid property, but let down by poor governance/customer service. That is inline with previous feedbacks I could read here.

Family of four from UK. Stayed three nights.

The bedrooms were small but entirely adequate. Good air conditioning - effective without being over powering. Good pillows. Lovely Clarins shower gel, shampoo and conditioner. Proper hangers (unusual these days). Lovely tiling and fittings in the bathrooms. Powerful shower. Excellent breakfast. Lovely restaurant, beautifully decorated.

Best of all was the flexibility of the staff. We had to change our booking twice because of Covid and on both occasions our changes were accommodated without a single quibble. Topping off this excellent service was a €100 reduction in our bill because instead of staying over New Year we stayed in July.

We booked a suite which turned out to be not acceptable for an Accor hotel. The second room was just a large bed which could not be moved and the rooms needed refurbishment. We were relocated to adjoining interconnected rooms which were infinitely better. The ladies on reception were exceptionall helpful, as was the man who booked a trip for us. They should all be promoted. The breakfast was exceptionally good and a big surprise. We did have a coffee machine in the room as well. Personally we did not like the area which is on the outskirts of the main shopping area, a bit like being in a hotel just off Oxford Street. We would not stay in that area again but full marks to all the staff.

I was not entirely satisfied. I have stayed at Accor hotels all over the world, including in France.
The hotel room was very nice. So were the common areas and the location. The surprising and disappointing thing at this hotel was the insufficiency of front desk employees and support. Sometimes there was not one employee at the front desk. You would have to wait and someone would come eventually. And to call in the evening, you would always have to wait 20 ring tones before someone picked up, appearing to be out of breath! We did not see luxury hotel service, as expected. Even during the morning, when there were two employees, they were overloaded and you would often have to wait. We stayed at an Accor M-Gallery (Royal) in Lyon, France. What a difference! Very attentive staff. Turn down service every night. Delivery of chocolates every night. Immediate reaction for any problem. L'Échiquier was disappointing on that level. Even for the check out, the front desk person did not ask me if we enjoyed our stay. Again, surprising for Accor hotel level. Contrary to other Accor hotels, I did not receive a request for a survey, which is standard practice. (only a suggestion to put something on trip advisor) They therefore seem to be aware of insufficient service support and do not want to hear about it or address it.

Lovely small hotel in 10th arronsidement. Nice neighborhood. Helpful staff at feint desk and restaurant. We held a business meeting here over the weekend-- good place for this. Room was small, but it's Paris. Comfortable bed and bathroom. Try to avoid rooms along street, which was my situation, as it's loud with young people at night.

A very nice hotel in a great place ink Paris. From outside and at the lobby, one might misjudge this place. But you need top get in. The rooms are clean and elegant. The restaurant is extremely good, in looks and cuisine.

Good service and great meeting rooms.

As every hotel in Paris the rooms are tiny!But a clean hotel close to all amenities with helpful staff the kitchen not so tasty with very few selections. But a very central area to stay close to metro station.

I am afraid I do not agree with all the glorious reviews of this hotel. It is very average for the price you pay and the service is poor. The rooms (even the superior ones) are very small (ok, ok, it is Paris), you pay the price tag for it and there are many other hotels in the same location. The big let down is actually the service: okish breakfast but nothing special, no coffee machines in the room, just cheap kettle, no towels (we had to ask them every single day to bring towels - I am sorry but is it so difficult?!), no ironing board (again you need to ask for it), no bottle opener, room not done by 5pm despite the sign on the door since 10am in the morning and I has even to ask for toilet paper (ridiculous). The bar downstairs has a nice Art Deco but again very pricey for what you get. I am not sure I would stay here again at all and not at the same price. As written in other reviews, they also tried to charge us some additional taxes and they got very unpleasant when I challenged them. Finally, they realized the mistake (as I already paid them) and refunded. The staff at the reception has no clue in how to run a hotel (also written in other reviews). Look for better options as the service is very poor.

The hotel is very well decorated in a Art Deco set up.

Service room and cleanliness are good and in line with price point. The bathroom is particularly large.

The bar and restaurant offers good value options.

The hotel is close to the metro and a stone away from lively restaurants, bars and theaters.

Highly recommended.

Stayed for four nights over New Year’s. We arrived early after an overnight flight from New York and even though I requested early check in, we were told the room wouldn’t be ready until 2 pm. Had drinks, an early lunch and hit the Rodin Museum. Came back after 2 and the room still wasn’t ready. But they offered us two free drinks while we waited longer which was really only a couple of minutes. The hotel concierge was very responsive to my incessant questions around COVID testing, arranging an amenity for a friend’s birthday (which I had to retract since they canceled last minute), as well as holding a gift that a friend left at reception for our arrival. We stayed in a junior suite which was quite spacious with a separate deep soaking tub and rainfall shower. The only quirk with the room was that the bathroom door wouldn’t stay open on its own, so we used the slippers as a makeshift door stopper. We also couldn’t figure out how to turn the heat off in the room, but luckily it was quiet outside (we faced the courtyard) so we could sleep with the window open. Loved the Clarins products and the fact that they were not in individual bottles so more eco friendly.

We used the fitness room each morning which only had other guests the first morning. Protocol said only two people in the room at time, but there were four of us for a total of about 15 minutes. The other three mornings, we were the only ones. Small gym but there was chilled water and towels. Though no sanitizing products to clean the machines.

The location was pretty central to reach a lot of sites by walking including Musee d’Orsay and Musee de l’Orangerie as well as some great restaurants.

All of the staff that we interacted with were friendly and accommodating of my poor French. Even putting up with my angry husband when he couldn’t figure out how to type the reception email correctly in order to print out our negative COVID tests.

I would highly recommend the hotel and look forward to another stay.

All hotel team members are all highly professional, supportive and diligent in any type of need and request we had.
Hotel is ideally located and super comfortable, sound insulation and bedding quality ate over the top !

Stayed over for new years eve, the hotel is nice with a chi old times vibe.Had dinner for New year, which was good. When leaving, I forgot a bag, called reception, and when came to get it, my perfume was missing which was the only thing of value in the bag, I could see someone went through the bag and searched it. I dont like false accusations, but shocked by this insecurity,
Keep your belongings safe if you choose this place.

A very nice pleasant stay in Paris, one of the nicest that I had in Paris. Very nice location, services and room facilities.
We enjoyed a great weekend in Paris and the choice of this hotel helped a lot for our wellbeing.

Perfect stay for our family of 4 with two children. The location is ideal, only a couple of minutes walk from the metro with good quick connections to most of the tourist areas. We were also able to walk to the hotel easily from arriving in Paris at the Gare du Nord and found lots of good restaurants and cafés on the main road nearby. We were upgraded to two interconnected rooms which were ideal, with comfortable beds, and they were very quiet. The breakfast was superb, lots of choice and everything of very high quality. The staff were all welcoming and helpful, and very family friendly, eg. making our two children hot chocolate with straws at breakfast time. We'd love to stay here again next time we are in Paris.

You know the agony: should you bring your own hair dryer with you on vacation, or risk using the hotel’s? You could end up trying to style your hair with a dryer that appears to be run by squirrels.

But not at this hotel. And that, my friends, is a metaphor for our experience there.

We bookended a river cruise with stays at this hotel. It is a beautiful space, and the rooms are comfortable and quiet. The bathroom is modern and well-stocked (including the aforementioned hair dryer, a veritable Porsche of hair dryers!). The breakfast, though pricey (26E pp), had an excellent range of choices. My only complaint is that the rooms were both very warm, we couldn’t get the thermostat to cool it down enough and had to sleep with the windows open (it was still quiet btw).

The front end of our trip was awesome: excellent guidance on restaurant choices, professional and helpful front desk staff. I want to call 2 staffers out by name: Hoda and Shawn, who got me through a MasterCard disaster that left us high and dry on cash.

The back end of our trip was not as great as the first— things seemed not as crisp (housekeeping forgot to clean our room, then ignored a written note on the bed (in French) asking for more towels), front desk forgot to order our 6:30 am taxi to the airport, also struggled to print out our bill, the front desk guy who checked us in seemed annoyed by my questions about COVID testing, etc.). But again kudos to Hoda who came through with a reservation for the BEST RESTAURANT of our entire trip.

I wish I could give 5 stars to Hoda and 4.5 for the hotel, because they were near perfect.

The hotel is in a great location. The reception staff are very attentive and pleasant. The bar/ restaurant staff are equally pleasant too. We stayed in a superior double room which was spacious and very clean, over looking the street, which was ok, after all we are in a city. This can be a little noisy if the window is open at night. The only one disappointing thing for me, was that I’d have liked a drawer in the room to place underwear/socks. The breakfast is nice and lots of choice but the hot buffer was limited to scrambled eggs, sausage and bacon.

The bathroom was clean and I enjoyed the use of the Clarins products. There is tea/coffee available in the room which is of a very good quality.

There is a safe in the room which is one of the easiest ones I’ve ever used.

More hangers in the wardrobe, would be a bonus!!

I couldn’t fault the hotel.

Be very careful when travelling on the Metropolitan, make sure you don’t have your phone out on show and don’t be flashing any expensive jewellery.. keep your watch covered up or don’t where one at all. This is a great way to get around in Paris and a day ticket only costs €7.50.

The hop on/hop off river cruise is a great way to get around Paris too. This is around €19 for a day ticket.. we made use of this and it stops at all the popular attractions.

Have your wits about you whilst in Paris, as many cities across the world, there are pickpockets/opportunists around.

Fabulous place to shop, there is a nice part of Paris which is around 1.5miles from the hotel, here you’ll find lots of very nice expensive shops (bring your credit card with you!). This part is also home to the French Prime Minister!

There’s plenty of bars and restaurants to choose from.

Very nice hotel in a great area of town. We used the metro a lot to get around Paris as it is a 5 minute walk to the nearest station. There are several great restaurants around.

The room itself was nice and clean the whole visit. The room was not ready as promised at 3pm and the front desk didn’t really have an answer why.

This hotel is located in walking distance from Gare du Nord, in a small street, looking squeezed between the Opera and other houses. But when you enter you are welcomed very friendly in a cozy and astonishing world of Belle Époque architecture. We particularly liked the bar/restaurant/breakfast environment and the elevator design.

Very friendly team, super professional always eager to help and listen
Ideal location in a very Parisian district a bit like meatpackers.
Very central París a mile away from the Seine river, 1 mile away from Saint Martin Canal. At the very heart of what París is supposed to be. Alternative, inventive, messy what philosophy is about. All men are equal

Good hotel at a central location. Friendly staff. Breakfast was good, but not a cosy place for diner. In the area enough fine restaurants where you can eat for a decent price. Paris Nord station (Thalys) is just a 15 minute walk.

A perfect hotel experience. Extremely professional and experienced in hospitality. This is a four star establishment but managed better than lots of supposedly 5 star Accor establishments, like Sofitel Strasbourg which is a complete disaster (full review posted last week). The website description of the hotel and the rooms is 100 per cent accurate. We stayed in their largest suite and it was excellent and spacious and well furnished. The bar downstairs makes great cocktails. The breakfast is delicious and always served with a smile. The front desk staff are helpful and friendly in an unobtrusive manner. The location is between best of both sides of the city. On the one hand you are close to hip new places full of young energy, but at the same time you are walking distance to the old glamour. The taxi fare to the hotel from Gare Du Lyon is approximately 30 euros with tip.

I came when COVID testing requirements were fluctuating regularly. I stayed for six nights and it was very stressful having to get tested every 72 hours plus get the PCR test to leave the country. The staff helped me set up Covid appointments and were incredibly patient with me and my meltdowns (thank you to all of the staff). The hotel room (419) was spacious, beautiful, very quiet, clean and comfortable. It was close to the Bonne Nouvelle Metro stop and so many restaurants along that street. I would definitely stay here again.

We really enjoyed our stay. The building was full of character (the good kind), beautifully finished and comfortably modernised in tune with the original architecture. Staff were attentive yet discreet. Breakfast was a treat and we slept amazingly well. I’d love to go back again.

Very nice hotel, second time we are staying in MGallery and still very satisfied: rooms are comfortable, breakfast is excellent, location is perfect, closed to many Parisian spots, staff was very friendly. We will come back

Our trip was actually back in March of 2019 and we (Steve & Kim) reflect back on it with fond memories. We enjoy going through the pictures of our visit and are reminded what a good time we had. L'Echiquier was an excellent choice for exploring Paris. The hotel is close to the Metro and we got pretty good at getting around on it. We enjoyed the food in Paris very much starting with the Petit Dejeuner at L'Echiquier. We spent plenty of time at the L'Amore Vache for meals and drinks, which is just around the corner and down the street from L'Echiquier. Everyone we came across on our visit was helpful and friendly starting with the staff at the front desk at L'Echiquier. We will not forget Youssouf, the Dining Room Manager. He was especially kind to us and selected cheeses for us to try. Thanks so much Youssouf, we think about you every time we try to find a decent cheese here in the USA. Of the four cheeses you picked for us I liked the Brie, and your favorite, Comte the best. We purchased some Macaroons at a Boulongerie close to L'Echiquier to take home on our last night in Paris. A fellow customer translated our order for us, as our French could be much better. The owner sent us home with a bag full of pastries and baguettes as she was closing up. Just more examples of how wonderful we were treated in Paris. We would definitely stay again at L'Echiquier and hope to come back soon. Hope you all have avoided the Covid mess, stay well my friends!

Spent two nights in Paris at this hotel. Honestly it made me forget that we are in a world crisis. All the safety precautions are met and it is very warm and charming. I arrived a little late and they made sure I could still get some food. Ordered some room service and it was very nice (there is an error so I can’t upload pictures). The best part of the hotel is the staff. They are truly keen on giving excellent service and always give that little extra attention. A real asset and they should be cherished. Ali at breakfast is a darling and a young man at reception daytime.... unfortunately didn’t catch his name, made me feel like coming back. This will be my go to address from now on! Thank you for a lovely stay. The room was clean, except for a little dust on the night stand everything was perfect. I had a wonderful dinner and some lunch but didn’t take any pictures.
See you soon!

Despite the challenging time the hotel is open and running. Kudos to all the employees! It's very handy to have a restaurant in house. Not only for the spectacular breakfast but also to have a bite to eat when everything around there is closed.

Beautiful boutique hotel in an old Art Deco building, perfectly located in the center of Paris, close to the Opéra and Place de la Concorde. Nicely decorated rooms in art deco style, comfortable bed, Clarins cosmetics, good quality breakfast. Nice staff and correct hotel management, thank you very much to the whole hotel team, we will come again!

I stayed at L'Echiquier for about a week in these very special circumstances and it felt like home. They're being very careful to follow all the social distanciation rules and I have to say it's very convenient to have a bar/restaurant in house while there is a curfew in place.

Chose this hotel on the Accord website, with a specific request for a car park.
This hotel came up on the list, in reality it doesn't have a car park, there is public one around the corner 500m away. On the hotel page it does say it's "in the proximity" of the hotel.
So I missed that.
The second point that was really annoying, due to an accident on the motorway we arrived at 22h30. At the reception there way a fantastic guy, really kind and as helpful as anyone could be, but he was an "Extra" who knew very little about the hotel, and there was no one else from the hotel in the place with him. We asked for room service, and he told us there was no room service available ! I understand that there are limitations due to Covid 19, but not even a bit of bread and cheese !

All that said, the hotel is very good, well worth a visit. Room was super clean and breakfast while expensive was really good as well.

All the staff are really helpful.

My stay in August was my second stay at the MGallery l’Echiquier and it was excellent. The room was great and the client service even better. I particularly enjoyed the staff’s attention to clients with the tea time offered in the afternoon.
I definitely recommend this hotel and will come back when I’m back in Paris.

L’échiquier is an excellent hotel in Paris - four stars yet the service and amenities feel like a five star hotel. Staff is very attentive to the guests’ needs and are very helpful. Rooms are decorated with taste and style, and the bar/lounge area is a nice place to relax in after long walks in Paris. I will definitely come back for my next stay in Paris!

Excellent hotel within a very good location. Great service. The Staff is very friendly. The hotel is carefully maintained, even in this pandemic time. It was my second time here and for sure not the last one.

We thoroughly enjoyed our week long stay at the L'Echiquier Hotel. The staff were very helpful especially when my husband needed assistance after a traumatic experience on the Metro. The staff were able to get us in touch with banks etc and spent a good deal of time helping us to sort out our problem. The room was clean and comfortable with all the amenities we needed. There is a restaurant in the hotel which provided breakfast and dinner at a reasonable cost. We were within walking distance of the Metro and many restaurants and shopping opportunities.
We would happily stay here again!

The Staff at Hotel L'Echiquier Opera Paris were amazing, friendly, easy work work with, speak excellent english. Our room was beautiful, by Paris standards it was large. The breakfast buffet was wonderful. Walking distance to Metro lines 8 and 9 allowed us to get anywhere in Paris in no time at all. And the rooms were very quite. No city sounds or neighbor sounds.

I was very excited to go as it was a present from my friend. Hotel located in a district with plenty entertainment and food options. The room is of a good size, but nothing compared to asian 4* hotels. The biggest problem was the stuff however, they showed a really poor attitude. There was a special arrangement booked for the room and they kept on giggling about it which didnt give any relaxing welcoming feeling. Also when I ordered a wine opener from the bar the guy came extremely annoyed. Wouldnt stay there again.

As Brits, we don’t mind a walk, so this was in a great spot, as we were in our room within twenty minutes of clambering off the Eurostar. The staff were all friendly and helpful. The room wasn’t small, the bed was very comfortable and I’m in love with Clarins so thoroughly enjoyed their products. Breakfast was excellent and varied and we loved the free afternoon tea and cake too. I would wholeheartedly recommend this hotel which we booked as part of our Eurostar package.

The hotel is nice but I must say we were amazed by the level of service or the various errors by the Front Office staff while we stayed there. I would have given it 5 stars but to us, it seemed we were dealing with "amateurs". Calls at 10.30pm in the room and front office staff showing up at the door to check if the room was occupied, guest entering our room while we

We booked our first trip to Paris through Costco. The package included airfare, transportation from and to the airport and hotel accommodations including the daily buffet. This hotel location was perfect for touring the city. The hotel staff (English speaking) were very polite and helpful in assisting with local attractions. They provided a city map and also printed out walking directions.

Louvre Museum - 30 minute walk
Opera area - 22 minute walk
Galleria area - 22 minutes
Eiffel Tower - metro 9 rail (be sure to walk to a station that includes staffed service to purchase metro tickets. The one closest to the hotel only accepts tickets already purchased. The hotel staff forgot to mention that detail)

The hotel itself was fairly nice but we did experience problems with heating/ac unit. The Clarins products provided were absolutely wonderful. The restaurant provides a daily buffet which was decent; however, we’re not necessarily breakfast people. The restaurant is lacking for dinner options so be prepared to eat out at night. Also note at night after a long day touring the city, the TV only included French speaking stations - which is not a big deal.

The hotel recommended the Laduree (which is well know ) for macaroons; however, I preferred the ones from the cafes at the Louvre Museum and the Eiffel Tower. There is also a local bakery that has the best pastries ever down from the hotel (see my review)!!!! Zazza’s is right at the corner and had wonderful pizza and Moscato d’Asti wine.

Thanks to the staff for making this a wonderful first visit to Paris. I will definitely stay here again.

We had a wonderful stay here at The Hotel LEchiquier Opera Paris. The staff were accommodating and kind. The location is excellent as most everything is just a short walk and/or metro ride away. The food was also of the finest quality and we felt quite spoiled.
If the hotel sees this: can you kindly tell me what the scent is that envelopes you when you walk into the lobby? I know everything in the rooms was Clarins (luxurious) is this a Clarins fragrance that can be purchased? I can't find an email to ask. Thank you. Plantmum6@gmail.com

We spent 3 nights at this hotel (room 307 from 2.1 to 5.1.2020) and was really a disappointing experience.

The hotel is located near to metro station. However, in case of strike of public transports in Paris, the location is really not convenient.

All the employees of the reception were particularly kind, professional and pro-active. A big THANKS for all the employees at reception, congratulations!

The location of the hotel is also very good and convenient. Many nice restaurants just around the hotel.

The real main negative point was the not sufficient cleaning of the room.

When we arrived our double room had only 1 shower towel for 2 people!!!
I immediately tought to a mistake, but the bellboy confirmed that the hotel did not had any additional towel in the entire hotel! The hotel had a problem with the bed lines and towel delivery, which is unacceptable for a MGALLERY Hotel.

The kind receptionist went to different rooms in order to collect extra towels for our room. Sounds surreal for a MGallery hotel...

In addition the level of cleaning of the room and bathroom was not so accurate for an hotel of this category.

No bathrobe and no slippers provided. Only when I asked, they recognized that the cleaning lady forgot this well.

In the room were only 1 pair of slippers which were already used (i.e. you were able to see the footprint on the slipper!). The receptionist apologies for this.

The bed lines were also not completely clean. One cover for pillow was clearly dirty!

The hotel apologies for this inconvenience and even offer a room upgrade, which I refused.

I think that a minimal level of cleaning MUST be a standard in EVERY room for an hotel of this category.

The safe in the room is suitable also for pc laptop. I left my tablet in the safe. However, the minibar is exactly under the safe, which made the safe and your tablet/pc extremely warm! This can destroy your pc battery!

In addition the service at the bar and breakfast buffet was really poor. The employees were more busy to chat with each other rather than to be focussed on clients. At the breakfast many glasses were also not clean, which show a general low level of cleaning at this hotel. In addition small gnats were always flying near to food at breakfast.

The hotel itself was nice and cosy. Unfortunately the level of cleaning needs to be improved. Bed lines MUST be clean and towels need to be provided in a sufficient quantity. This should be a minimal service for a MGallery hotel.

I visited many hotels in Paris and this experience was clearly disappointing. The employees at the reception were really kind and professional. Therefore there is room for global improvement.

A clean room is the first luxury!

Very comfortable hotel next to restaurants, bars and shops.
The staff is very friendly and helpful.
I had a complaint about an used (and dirty) pillow left in my room on the day of my arrival. It got changed right away.
Breakfast was really really good.
I would definitely stay here again

Stayed one night in October and fell in love within this property. It’s beautifully finished, respecting the historic nature of the building while ensuring guest comfort. The staff are charming and smile as if they like jobs. He bar/restaurant is a beautiful area with a pleasant ambience. The location works well wiht multiple metro and bus options nearby. Tricky with the train strikes but we walked more than ever to compensate. A great choice in
Paris. I will be back

The Hotel LEchiquier Opera Paris is a very nice and beautiful hotel in a central location close to Montmartre, Louvre, Galleries Lafayette and Garnier Opera. It is very clean and quiet, and staff is very friendly. The rooms are very clean and comfy, and have fridge and kettle. The bathroom’s toiletries are all top range from Clarins that makes you feel very special! We didn’t have breakfast at the hotel, but had dinner and room service and food was great! They beautifully decorated the hotel for Christmas and had a live singer and piano player on New Year Day - felt like a perfect first day of the year. A tourist tip - the hotel has a great authentic Parisian bakery nearby called Julhes for croissants and baguettes - highly recommend to try their different pastry and cakes.

My partner and I spent the four days following Christmas travelling on Eurostar to Paris on a package deal that included this gem.

My first impression on approaching it from the road was simplicity and humble but when I went through the doors into the Foyer, it was the beginning of a classy experience.

As you come in the reception is to your left, it was a simple and straightforward experience with an introduction to the restaurant straight ahead. We did not choose to have breakfast but had we it would have cost €26 each.

The restaurant itself is surprisingly spacious. The Hotel puts on a complimentary afternoon Tea from 1430 to 1700 where one can partake of a selection of teas, coffee and a wide selection of patisserie in quiet and tasteful surroundings.

The Hotel has six floors, I would not say it was wheelchair friendly unless there were rooms I did not see on the first floor.

The elevator whilst charming is totally unsuitable for a wheelchair unless it can be folded up and the occupant stand for the upward and or downward journey.

Our room 202 was on the second floor and faced the road. It was very warm, even with the heating off!

The Hotel is a Clarin's Hotel and all the dispensers in the bathroom were clarins products.

The bathroom was compact, it would not suit a disabled person, the toilet was much too low and set in a tight spot between the lovely shower and the wall. This said it was spotless and contained a hairdryer and ample towels of differing sizes including a face towel each!

The shower is a large walk in variety, with a waterfall head set into the roof and a hand held shower unit for convenience. It is raised off the ground day about five inches and if you are a little unsteady on your feet could be lethal because the shower tray floor is very smooth. I was very careful going in and coming out.

The room sported a large TV wall mounted with ample English programmes. It had a large cupboard which also housed the easy to use safe and glass fronted refrigerator.

The bed was large and comfy, we found it a little too warm for comfort but otherwise well appointed.

Location wise the Hotel was easy access to the main streets and theatres of the Opera area. It took 15 minutes to walk to it from Gare du Nord and about 2 hours to walk back from the Eiffel Tower on account of the strike about pensions there was limited public transport.

There are plenty of places to eat around the Hotel.

The reception and other staff were helpful and efficient.

We enjoyed our stay here and would be happy, subject as above, to recommend it to you.

We enjoyed our five day stay. Hotel was nicely decorated for Christmas. Excellent breakfast and the day we left they allowed us in early so we had time before our driver arrived. Afternoon tea excellent as well. Our room was clean and comfortable. Would stay again. Excellent location for walking to museums and sights.

Finding a hotel room for a family of four in Paris is not easy. However, hotel L’Échiquier Opera was the perfect choice for us. I reserved this cozy suite with a sofa bed and two bathrooms. It was not big but very comfortable and cozy.

We could get anywhere very easily. Lots of nice restaurants nearby and near the metro as well. The hotel is quite small but has a unique style. I could feel the old world charm from walking down the hallway to riding on a tiny elevator. The beautiful sun lit dining area was super relaxing. Breakfast was very fresh and delicious with great selection of French pastries.

Everyone was very friendly and helpful especially to the children. Front desk gave nice suggestions of what to do for kids during our stay. I highly recommend this hotel and would definitely return for the next trip to Paris.

We were really pleased to have stayed at this hotel. We felt welcomed and well taken cared of from the moment we checked-in. All the staffs were very polite and helpful with our concerns. The room that we had was very spacious and complete with everything we needed. Thank you so much for giving us an upgrade. The hotel is surrounded with several restaurants and we ate at a few of them and were very pleased overall. The breakfast buffet at the hotel was amazing and the design and layout of this area is very elegant. We really liked it. We would not hesitate to stay here again on our next trip to Paris.

The boutique hotel is comfortable, has character and friendly staff. As on previous visits we were well looked after during our stay. The location works well for us. We really like the restaurant/bar area.

Consistency with staff attention, friendliness and excellent service. My only wish for change would be the beds. Too soft for someone with chronic back pains. Room with the balcony is amazing! Thank you.

The hotel is located in a very good neighborhood. At night, it is quiet and bustling during the day. It is 2 minutes away from the subway station. Also close to Gare de Lyon if you need to take the train from there to Belgium.

Check in was smooth. We arrived early after a red eye flight and was able to check in early.

The building was built on the previous King’s hunting house

Our Deluxe room is actually big for Paris standard with the view of the neighborhood. Sometimes it it a bit awkward when you go out to the balcony and the Parisian neighbors across the street make eye contact with you.

The bathroom uses Clarins products so additional plus points.

It was our honeymoon so the staffs went above and beyond to make us feel special.

Overall a solid experience within the more affordable pricing.

As per the title above - hotel meets most selection criteria for both business & leisure travel to Paris (in this budget category). Room size is average, but that is not different from most hotels in Paris.

Stayed here for the weekend as it is a couple of streets away from Le Grand Rex, where I was seeing New Order play the Paris leg of their tour. I was upgraded to a superior room upon arrival, a nice peaceful room on the top floor of the hotel. The area it’s in is a bit out of the way from the main tourist areas of Paris(approximately 10 minutes by foot to the Opera district and Galeries Lafayette) and I don’t know if I’d here stay here again unless I was going to something like the concert but I liked the hotel (and it’s friendly, helpful staff) and it was reasonably priced.

Stayed for a night at this hotel on a business trip.

The hotel staff is very friendly and helpful.

The breakfast spread is decent.

The bed is very cozy and comfortable.

The only minus for me is the room sizes.

I was pleasantly surprised by this hotel. The location was great because we could easily walk to the Louvre, Sacre Coeur, the river, Marais and Bastille for great restaurants, the Opera and Galeries Lafayette. We loved to walk too. But on days where we needed to take public transportation the Bonne Nouvelle Metro station was a short walk away.
Breakfast was good and the wait staff was very friendly and helpful. The front desk personnel were nice and we were able to check in early with no problems. The room was small but very comfortable. The Clarins products were a nice touch and smelled wonderful. Our room faced the street but the noise at night was not bad, we slept well. The neighborhood was very lively during the day and night. Lots of restaurants, groceries, bakeries and cafes. I would stay here again.

Really liked this hotel. Modern, clean, superb staff throughout. Room on floor 6 very nice with a view to Montmartre. Spacious with large comfortable bed and excellent bathroom. Great breakfast with plenty of choice. Good location with plenty of cafes, bars & eateries within easy walking distance. Only 15/20 minute walk to Galerie Lafayette district where you'll find world class shopping on Boulevard Haussman & easy for metro. Highly recommend.

Very nice hotel in Paris. Staff was friendly and helpful. We needed to confirm a tour, and when the phone in our room didn't work, a staff member called for us. Breakfast buffet is extensive and delicious.

This is Mc Gallery hotel what means unique design, comfortable rooms and very very nice atmosphere. Staff is very polite, always helpfull, and rooms are nice. Bed is big, comfortable and calls for a good sleep. Bathroom is also spacious and clean.

I am an Accor Platinum member. We had pre-booked 2 separate stays In Hotel L'Echiquier Opera Paris prior to departing Australia, a 1 night & a 3 night stay. For convenience we had breakfast in the hotel for the overnight staying under the assumption it was a free breakfast as is the case for Platinum members in Australia & Asia. Upon checking out I was surprised it wasn't free & didn't receive a friendly or informative response even though I was happy to pay for it. Upon returning for our second stay we found ourselves in the most furthest away room in a terrible position & the staff made a point of telling us on check-in that it wasn't a free breakfast. They made us feel unwelcomed & we really regretted staying there even though. The customer service was terrible and has made me question my loyalty to the Accor group. It was about the reception we received from the staff and the fact we felt like we were shoved out the back to teach us a lesson. I will not recommend this hotel as customer service should be the highest priority as that is what always brings return travellers. Its a shame.

I stayed several times at this hotel whenever I’m in Paris.
Usually the rooms are comfortable and spacious, however you might end up in smaller rooms, so double check on this when making the reservation.
The reception staff is always very kind and responsive. The staff at the breakfast restaurant is very nice and fast, and the breakfast variety is consistent with lots of pastries, jams, fresh orange and grapefruit juices. You can find scrambled eggs, but I’ve never asked for poached eggs or a omelette, so not sure if they make them. The cappuccino ain’t great though.
The rooms are clean and quiet.
The location is very good and you can find good restaurants nearby.

Although we have announced that we will arrive around 13 o'clock, upon arrival the room was not ready. At my insistence I received room 517, a room with a much smaller surface. I refused room 517 and received, after 3 pm, an appropriate room, 417.
Breakfast is very limited, poor; only one sort of eggs, 3 sorts of salami and 3 sorts oh cheese. And I asked for champagne / prosecco, I got the menu from the bar, where a glass of champagne costs 15 euros.
A few days before I stayed at Mercure Montparnasse, where breakfast was much better!
This is not the standard MGallery!

This hotel is going through refurbishment at the moment, so there's a little noise now and again, but your'e going to be out all day, so what. To be honest it does need work done to the rooms, they are clean but showing their age in many areas. If you can book a refurbished room before arriving you will not be disappointed, they have done a fantastic job on them. The staff are all very helpful and all seem to speak English very well. There are many bistros and cafes within strolling distance so if you don't fancy the hotel breakfast just pop out and have a coffee and croissant ( about 5 euros)

Very nice hotel in The heart of Paris. The staff is very friendly and useful. Nice comfi rooms good beds and it's quiet and calm. A very nice address in Paris. The breakfast is healthy and there are many different things to choose from. This is a +++++hotel

I loved our stay here. The room wasn’t huge, but spacious enough for our small family and tastefully decorated. The bathroom was lovely, with Clarins products, although the soap wasn’t replaced.

Soft drinks were replenished daily, which was very helpful, but tea, coffee and milk need to be added to more frequently. Air con. worked well and was comfortable.

The staff was excellent, professional and friendly. The breakfast staff went over and above to ensure that guests were enjoying their stay. We found breakfast very good, with an array of choice.

Excellent location, with métro station close, as were restaurants. Only a short walk to most of the main sights of Paris.

Just a few small housekeeping tweaks and it would be perfect! We all loved Hôtel l’Échiquier and look forward to our next visit. Recommended.

We booked a junior suite here expecting a king bed (as per the description) as we were staying seven nights. Our room was ok but we weren't given a king bed as described online. When we questioned this, we were told that families were given priority for the king bed configuration and that as we were unhappy it would be raised with the manager. We did not hear back.

Housekeeping was also a bit slack - coffee, tea and toiletries not replaced and we had to ask for our sheets to be changed.

Also on checkout we had been charged for breakfasts that we hadn't had. This was cheerfully amended but be aware.

However, it is in a good location and staff were helpful.

I love this hotel and this was my 4th visit there. The rooms are well thought out, beautifully clean and very practical. The staff are efficient and very friendly. The dining room is a work of art and the food is delicious.
The position of the hotel is very convenient for Gare du Nord, as it is easy walking distance. I can easily walk from the hotel down to the centre of Paris and all the well known landmarks there. There are 3 Metro stations within a few minutes walk of the hotel if they are needed. There is even a Post Office around the corner.

The hotel was wonderful. It was centrally located to all the sites we want to see, and if they were further the metro was very easy to access. The staff was exceptional, always willing to assist and help with any Paris questions.

Stayed here with my wife for 4 nights and could not fault the hotel, it’s staff or the location. From the first minute we arrived the staff were friendly, attentive and extremely efficient. They even helped us as we practiced our French. The bar area is a fantastic location to sit and have a relaxing drink, the food was excellent too. We loved our stay here and will be returning very soon.

I stayed here for a total of 7 nights for a holiday in Paris. I decided to stay at this hotel upon reading the excellent reviews from many websites. I can say certainly that this hotel lives up to its great reviews. The staff were good. The room was clean and comfy. Location is also very good. It is near many restaurants and there is a metro station nearby so it's convenient to go anywhere by public transportation. But what impressed me the most was the bathroom and the room amenities. The bathroom was exceptionally clean and I love the Clarins soap and shampoo. The bathroom instantly made me feel at home.

Great and Memorable stay. Definitely a quintessential Mgallery/Sofitel experience and I definitely would love to come back here next time I go to Paris.

Very Good Hotel, Very clean, Will give service a 5 Star. The staff very helpful and always smiling. Breakfast has good choice. Complementary Tea in afternoon is really a hit. Location close to 2 metro station. Lot of eating joints nearby. 10 min walking to shopping streets.

Our trip advisor that we use suggested three hotels to choose from. We chose this one because it was near the Main Street which was close to restaurants, shopping, the metro etc. He had told us that a four star is not what we expect a four star hotel would be in the United States. That helped to know that information so our expectations weren’t as high. Our room was small with no dresser or drawers anywhere, even the nightstands. There were three hangers so we had to have our clothes folded on chairs, table etc. luckily it wasn’t hot weather otherwise the air conditioning wouldn’t have been cool enough. We were gone a lot , mainly got back to the hotel late and watched some TV and went to bed. The breakfast was cheese plate, fruit, cereal, toast, scrambled eggs, bacon sausage etc.
I drink iced tea and found they serve it in bottles and it’s peach flavored at almost all places we visited. The people were helpful and friendly. Walked about 2 blocks to the main road in town.

This hotel is quite classy and the room we stayed in on the 6th floor was very clean with a basic but not unpleasant view. Bed was comfortable and service from staff was professional and friendly. The location itself was quite a distance from the main tourist spots but was interesting in itself as it showed more of the locals enjoying themselves at the local drinking spots. Plenty of eating options and close to Bonne Nouvelle Metro Station. No hesitation in recommending

Quaint hotel in a quiet area, nice decor, air con excellent in what was a hot week. Stayed 2 nights in what was charged as a superior room, tiny right next to the lift... i wouldnt have liked to stay in the basic room if mine was superior. Overpriced for the area, poor wi-fi and room space. My biggest complaint was when we went to the bar at 6pm for a pre-dinner drink to be told it was closed for a private function! No allowances left for guests but told we could have room service , in the tiny room with nowhere to sit! Laughable and a first for me in any hotel i have ever stayed at! Won’t return.

This is a charming 4-star hotel in the Sofitel group with a great, service-oriented staff. In my many trips to Paris, I can’t remember a staff who, to a person, tried to help as much as this one in every way requested (e.g. calls to Air France re a canceled flight, delivery of ice late at night). The rooms are small but well-appointed and the street is quiet at night, a real plus in this area. The one negative room issue was WiFi and data ports. We stayed in 2 different rooms at the beginning and end of a week of travel and in the first, the WiFi barely worked while in the 2nd it was fine. The one data port offered ONLY charges if the TV is on and it is very slow. Bring a converter and adapter – it came in useful for fast charging throughout the trip. The restaurant is in a beautiful space and offers a good morning breakfast with lots of variety and, as a treat for the guests, an afternoon spread of tea, coffee and snacks. The name implies that it is near the Opera but it is actually near the Porte Ste. Denis which is definitely away from the main tourist attractions. If you want a “local” experience, this is it but be prepared for all that means with regards to diversity and safety. The closest main street nearby, Blvd. Poissonniere, has quite a few restaurants and is very lively in the evenings but if you wander toward the Porte Ste. Denis gates, the feel is not quite as safe.

This is a beautiful hotel off a main thoroughfare in the heart of Paris. It's tucked away on a small, quiet side street but within walking distance of cafes, shops, transportation. The rooms are not huge but they're adequate, clean and well maintained. The restaurant/bar in the lobby has wonderful food whether you're enjoying breakfast buffet or ordering off the menu. And the staff is lovely and anxious to help with whatever you might need. Would definitely stay here again.
And if you need help with excursions, there's a wonderful Monogram's rep in the lobby to help. She was invaluable in augmenting what we'd already planned.

The hotel is tucked away on a small street. It is a block away from a major street to catch a Hop on Hop off Bus or take the subway. It is a beautiful building. The staff spoke English so we never had problems getting information. They were friendly. We enjoyed afternoon tea on of the days and it was excellent. Breakfast was good and there were ample items to choose from. We also walked there from the train station which is a little less than a mile away. Friendly and helpful staff made it a great place to stay.

Stayed for 3 nights in a de luxe room. Fresh flowers were a nice touch and there was indeed a view of Montmartre, but quite a bit of the floor space was a corridor with limited headroom facing the bathroom.

Breakfast buffet was OK, but have seen better in this class of hotel. Apart from that and a bar it had nothing else to offer. Location very secondary, though not far from Metro.

Basic bed and breakfast hotel.

We usually stay at another hotel in Paris, however, as we booked this trip fairly last minute that hotel was not available. As Accor Platinum members, we had stayed at the MGallery in Prague a few years ago and loved it, so we decided to check out this hotel. My husband contacted them directly and they gave us an excellent rate for a superior room (a few Euros cheaper than our usual hotel).

The hotel is located on a nice quiet side street just off the Boulevard de Bonne Nouvelle. It's an excellent location for walkers (which we are) and a two minute walk to the Bonne Nouvelle Metro stop. Easy access to all of the main points of interest via foot or subway.

The lobby is small but welcoming, and the elevator is amazing. There are also beautiful stained glass windows along the staircase. The bar is lovely, and with beautiful mosaic floors.

Our room was a great size and had everything we needed, including a fridge, safe, robes and slippers. The bed was very comfortable, as were the pillows (this is a very big deal to me!). Although had they not been, there was also a pillow menu which I loved.

The bathroom was great - a really good size, a shelf under the sink big enough for all of our toiletries, and a huge walk-in shower. I also loved that it had liquid soap (so much better than usual tiny bar soaps hotels have) and hand lotion affixed to the wall and not taking up room on the counter. And it was Clarins to boot, smelled so good.

We were provided two free bottles of water daily in our little fridge, one bottle of flat and one sparkling.

The staff were very helpful in storing our luggage when we first arrived (as our room was not yet ready), gave an excellent dinner recommendation, and helped us get a taxi to the airport at a pretty decent fare.

I also found this hotel to be extremely quiet. Other than the odd time hearing some people talking out on the street (our room was on the third floor), it was generally very peaceful, which is much needed when you're on vacation!

Bottom line, we loved it. Neither of us could come up with one negative thing to say about this hotel. I think we found our new favourite place to stay in Paris!

This hotel is in great condition and has a Parisian feel everywhere. It is in walking distance to the Louvre and Notre Dame (15-20 minutes) and to Galeries Lafayette (10 minutes). If you prefer to take the subway it is just a 1/4 mile away (Bonne Nouvelle). The area is full of young people with a lot of restaurants and cafes nearby. I will stay again!

Very nice, clean and well located hotel. Very clean, comfortable and spacious rooms and very good breakfast buffet. The staff was very nice and helpful. We really recommend this hotel and would stay there, again.

This hotel was amazing, we stayed here for two nights. My husband and I got in early and they were able to accommodate us and upgrade us for free. The room was large by Paris standards and the beds were so comfy. It was also super quiet. We had great service at the restaurant too!
